I am using it along with React-Select. I have a Creatable select component, wrapped in a <Controller/>. I need to modify the output of this select. if user selects default options, then it is stored in 'preset' array. if user creates options on his own, we need to store it in 'custom' array. 
So at the end we would have this structure: 
selectValue: {
   "preset": [
      {
        "label": "Interne Abteilungen",
        "value": 1
      },
      {
        "label": "Lieferanten",
        "value": 3
      }
    ],
    "custom": [
      {
        "label": "This is a custom entry"
      },
      {
        "label": "This is also a custom entry"
      }
}

In order to achieve the desired structure, you can use the `onChange` event provided by the `Controller` component from react-hook-form along with the `onCreateOption` event provided by react-select's Creatable component.

First, you need to set up your form and react-select component as follows:

```jsx
import { useForm, Controller } from "react-hook-form";
import Select from "react-select";

const MyForm = () => {
  const { control, handleSubmit } = useForm();

  const onSubmit = (data) => {
    console.log(data);
  };

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit(onSubmit)}>
      <Controller
        name="selectValue"
        control={control}
        defaultValue={{ preset: [], custom: [] }}
        render={({ field: { onChange, value } }) => (
          <Select
            isClearable
            isMulti
            options={options}
            // handle the select value change
            onChange={(selectedOptions) => {
              const presetOptions = selectedOptions.filter(
                (option) => !option.__isNew__ // assuming __isNew__ flag for custom options
              );
              const customOptions = selectedOptions.filter(
                (option) => option.__isNew__ // assuming __isNew__ flag for custom options
              );
              onChange({ preset: presetOptions, custom: customOptions });
            }}
            // handle creating custom options
            onCreateOption={(inputValue) => {
              const customOption = { label: inputValue };
              onChange({
                preset: value.preset,
                custom: [...value.custom, customOption],
              });
            }}
            value={value.preset.concat(value.custom)}
            // your additional props
          />
        )}
      />

      <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>
  );
};
```

In this example, `options` is an array of all the available options for the select component.

By using the `onChange` prop of the Select component, we handle the change event, which is triggered when an option is selected or deselected. We filter out the custom options based on the `__isNew__` flag, and update the corresponding `preset` and `custom` arrays in the form state.

Similarly, when a new option is created using the `onCreateOption` prop, we add it to the `custom` array in the form state.

Finally, upon form submission, you can access the form data, including the modified select value structure, in the `onSubmit` function.

This setup should allow you to achieve the desired output where the selected options are stored in the respective `preset` and `custom` arrays.

